The SmartCard API is a reference implementation of the SIMalliance Open Mobile API specification 
that will enable Android applications to communicate with Secure Elements, e.g. SIM card, embedded Secure Elements, Mobile Security Card or others.

The interface of the library is kept platform independent whereas the SmartcardService implementation is Android specific.

The current version from seek for android is V3.1.0.

org.simalliance.openmobileapi.jar and SmartcardService.apk are pre-built by MediaTek internal.

WHAT IT DOES?
=============
SmartcardService.apk contains 
 - SmartcardService Android remote service as the core of the smart card access
 - xxxTerminal Implementation of a Secure Element specific terminal, e.g. UiccTerminal or ASSDTerminal
 - Access Control Implementation of the Access Control Enforcer to control APDU access from Android applications

HOW IT WAS BUILT?
==================
SmartcardService.apk has been built. Therefore, you don't need build it.

HOW TO USE IT?
==============
Follow SIMalliance Open Mobile API specification and all APIs are available.